mistral.reason: Raúl Silva Henríquez was an Archbishop, but the title of "Roman Catholic archbishops" refers specifically to those who have been appointed as Archbishop in the Roman Catholic Church, and only during the 20th century. Since Silva Henríquez served as Archbishop from 1960 until 1990 (and died in 2004), he falls outside the scope of the category for 20th-century Archbishops.

qwen2.5.reason: Raúl Silva Henríquez served as Archbishop of Santiago from 3 May 1983 to 30 March 1990, which means he cannot be categorized as a 20th-century Roman Catholic archbishop since his tenure was in the early 21st century.
